50|$|The western <b>end</b> <b>of</b> the <b>platform</b> for tracks 1 and 3 and {{the eastern}} <b>end</b> <b>of</b> the <b>platform</b> for track 2 contain {{high-level}} sections <b>of</b> <b>platform.</b> Installed in 2004, these allow those with handicaps to board and bring the station in compliance with ADA regulations.|$|R
50|$|In 1987 twelve {{different}} horse sculptures by Kevin Atherton, titled Iron Horse, were erected between New Street {{station and}} Wolverhampton, including {{one at the}} southern <b>end</b> <b>of</b> <b>platforms</b> 2 and 3.|$|R
50|$|The station {{consists}} <b>of</b> {{an island}} <b>platform</b> serving two tracks. The station entrance {{is on the}} south side of the station, connected to the platforms by a footbridge at the east (Sakado) <b>end</b> <b>of</b> the <b>platform.</b> A footbridge served by lifts opened at the west (Ogose) <b>end</b> <b>of</b> the <b>platform</b> in 2009.|$|R
